      {
        "id": 3933530,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-11-17T19:00:32.306Z",
        "cooked": "<p>But they are not! Fonsalette is its own wine, from a separate estate in a different location. Declassified barrels from Rayas, Pignan and Fonsalette in turn end up in Pialade, which I guess is what you\u2019re thinking of.</p>\n<p>And nor is 2007 a stronger vintage. However, the 2007 Fonsalette is a lot less extreme in style than the 2007 Rayas.</p>",
